    "body": "In today's fast-paced industry, two developments are quietly revolutionising how quality is proven: digital **Manufacturing Record Books (MRBs)** and the fight against **counterfeit certificates**.\n\n## From paper MRBs to living records\nTraditionally, MRBs were paper-based — manual data entry, endless paperwork, and a binder assembled long after production finished. Digital MRBs capture and organise production data in real time, as the work happens, so the record is complete the moment a project closes.\n\n## Closing the door on counterfeit certificates\nCounterfeit certificates erode trust across the supply chain and can contribute to project failures. A digital, verifiable record makes a certificate's origin checkable — tracing heat numbers, verifying mills, and binding every approval to a real signature instead of a pasted image.\n\nSome of the benefits teams see almost immediately:\n\n- Higher efficiency and far less manual checking\n- Improved, rule-based quality control\n- Stronger traceability and data security\n- Real cost savings\n\nA trustworthy digital thread also lays the groundwork for accurate carbon accounting and, eventually, Digital Twins.",
